<TITLE> Addl Attorney General Siddiqui resigns </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com) Additional Attorney General Hasan Fayez Siddiqui Wednesday submitted his resignation through the Attorney General. Siddiqui deposited his resignation letter addressed to the President with the Attorney General's office at 11 am. "I'm resigning my office as of late I've been finding it increasingly difficult to discharge my duties as an Additional Attorney General," Siddiqui said in his letter of resignation. Abdul Quddus, administrative officer of the Attorney General's office told reporters, "After conducting an Appellate Division case in the morning, Hasan Fayez Siddiqui tendered his resignation. A special messenger carried the letter to law ministry." Siddiqui was appointed an Additional Attorney General on December 24, 2007. Earlier on June 1, Deputy Attorney General Anwarul Azim Khair Manna resigned his office. bdnew
